<h2><span style="font-weight: 400;">How Do Online Gold Dealers Work?</span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">When you buy gold online you want to deal with the people. The best online gold dealers get their gold directly from government places that make money from refineries and from suppliers. So when you order gold you pay the price of gold at that time. A little extra that helps the dealer pay for things and make some money. You also pay for making the gold into coins or bars.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once they get your money they pack up your order. Send it to you. They use companies, like FedEx or UPS to ship the gold and they make sure it is fully insured. You have to sign for the gold when it gets to your house. A lot of the online gold dealers will send your gold for free if you spend a certain amount of money. If you are buying gold for a kind of retirement account they will send the gold to a special place that is approved by the government not to your home.</span></p>
