<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">What is the most reputable gold dealer?</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Among reputable gold dealers with the longest track records, APMEX (founded 1999) and Lear Capital (founded 1997) have the most documented operating history. JM Bullion (founded 2011) has the highest verified customer review volume and won the 2026 Bullion Dealer of the Year award. All three hold A+ BBB ratings.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">What should I look for in the best gold bullion dealers?</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The key criteria for best gold bullion dealers are: A+ BBB rating, documented physical address, published premium over spot for each product, transparent buyback pricing, fully insured shipping, and a minimum of several hundred verified customer reviews. Premium transparency is the single most important factor. The best online bullion dealers display their buy and sell prices for every product before you add to cart.</span></p>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400;">Are Gold IRAs worth it?</span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">A Gold IRA can be worth it for investors seeking diversification from traditional paper assets in a tax-advantaged retirement account. The best gold IRA dealers like American Hartford Gold and Patriot Gold Group provide full rollover support.</span></p>
