</table>
<h3><b>The Pro-Rata Allocation Model &amp; Trading Availability</b></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The CAP TGE operates strictly on a </span><b>pro-rata allocation basis</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. This guarantees absolute fairness across the distribution network. Your final token allotment depends directly on the ratio of your committed BNB relative to the total collective BNB deposited by all participants during the two-hour window.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Once the subscription window successfully concludes, the acquired CAP tokens will be fully unlocked and made instantly available for live decentralized trading. Users can trade CAP directly on </span><b>Binance Wallet DEX</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or through </span><b>PancakeSwap liquidity pools</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Participant Qualification Note:</span></i><span style="font-weight: 400;"> To join through the Alpha event page, users must hold a minimum balance of </span><b>225 Binance Alpha Points</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Upon successfully entering the event, a deduction of </span><b>15 points</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> will be automatically applied to your account.</span></p>
<p><b><i>More Active Earn Programs: </i></b><a href="https://ventureburn.com/best-p2p-crypto-exchanges/" data-wpel-link="internal"><b><i>MEXC vs Binance 2026: Which Is 10 Best P2P Crypto Exchanges for Zero-Fee Trading in 2026the Better Crypto Exchange?</i></b></a></p>
<h2><b>Step-by-Step Guide: How to Participate</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">To avoid blockchain network congestion and secure your subscription allocation smoothly, follow these operational steps inside the application:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Step 1 &#8211; Access the Event Page:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Open your Binance Mobile App, switch over to the Web3 Wallet dashboard, and head to the active Alpha event portal to find the Cap TGE campaign section.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Step 2 &#8211; Verify Your Alpha Points:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Confirm that your account holds at least </span><b>225 Binance Alpha Points</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Ensure you are comfortable with the 15-point entry deduction requirement.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Step 3 &#8211; Fund Your Wallet:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Ensure your wallet holds a sufficient balance of native BNB on the </span><b>BNB Smart Chain (BSC)</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Remember that only backed-up Keyless Wallets created directly within Binance Wallet qualify. </span><i><span style="font-weight: 400;">Imported external software wallets or addresses that have been exported will be automatically disqualified.</span></i></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Step 4 &#8211; Commit BNB:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> The moment the subscription window opens at 10:00 AM UTC on June 26, enter your desired BNB allocation (up to 3 BNB) and confirm the transaction.</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><b>Technical Disclaimers &amp; Calculation Rules</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Before deploying capital into the decentralized subscription contract, please keep these structural parameters in mind:</span></p>
<p><b>Subscription Pricing Formula (Plain Text Format):</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The TGE token subscription price will be determined based on the BNB opening price one day before the announcement is made. The actual price you pay may differ from the real-time BNB price at the time of your subscription.</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Security Guardrails:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Beware of scams! Any CAP tokens found in general on-chain circulation prior to the official subscription period closing are fraudulent. Always double-check and confirm the official TGE contract address exclusively through Cap’s verified primary community channels.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Network Risks:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> The success of the decentralized subscription process relies heavily on the structural execution and operational capabilities of both the underlying blockchain and the project contract infrastructure. Due to potential congestion, subscription actions may lag or fail. Binance holds zero liability for transaction outcomes or any network gas fees spent during failed executions.</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;" aria-level="1"><b>Anti-Fraud Protocols:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Binance Wallet and the hosting project reserve the absolute right to disqualify a user’s reward and subscription eligibility if the underlying account is found to be involved in dishonest behaviors (e.g., wash trading, money laundering, self-dealing, bulk account registrations, or malicious market manipulation).</span></li>
</ul>
<h2><b>Project Overview: What is Cap (CAP)?</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cap functions as a highly transparent, blockchain-native </span><b>credit platform backed by robust financial guarantees</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The platform fundamentally revolutionizes how corporate and institutional credit markets access liquidity, replacing slow legacy banking pipelines with automated smart contract flows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">By integrating institutional-grade financial risk management with decentralized networks, Cap provides capital allocators with deep access to secure, yield-bearing real-world asset (RWA) credit structures. At the same time, it allows institutional borrowers to scale alternative financing lines quickly. Long-term, Cap aims to establish itself as the premier layer for collateralized credit markets, opening up programmatic debt coordination, alternative liquidity pools, and reliable yield frameworks for crypto-native capital worldwide.</span></p>
